          "text": "### Change\n\nIn `DeployVsixToExperimentalInstance`, after extracting the VSIX and touching `extensions.configurationchanged`, the test host now sets the extension as enabled in the registry **before** `devenv /updateconfiguration`:\n\n```57:66:c:\\Git\\codescene-vs\\Codescene.VSExtension.VS2022\\Codescene.VSExtension.VS2022.E2ETests\\ExperimentalInstanceDeploy.cs\n        ExtractVsix(vsixPath, extensionRoot);\n        TouchExtensionsConfigurationChanged(hiveRoot);\n        var vsInstanceId = Path.GetFileName(\n            hiveRoot.TrimEnd(Path.DirectorySeparatorChar, Path.AltDirectorySeparatorChar));\n        WriteExtensionEnabledInRegistry(vsInstanceId, identityId);\n\n        var updateExit = TestProcessRunner.RunExternalProcess(\n            devenvPath,\n            $\"/rootSuffix {E2ETestEnvironment.RootSuffix} /updateconfiguration\",\n```\n\n`identityId` is already the manifest `Metadata/Identity/@Id` from `ReadVsixIdentity`. `vsInstanceId` matches the experimental hive folder name (e.g. `17.0_…Exp`), same idea as `SuppressCopilotFreePromoNotification`.\n\nNew helper:\n\n```csharp\nprivate static void WriteExtensionEnabledInRegistry(string vsInstanceId, string extensionId)\n{\n    var keyPath = $@\"Software\\Microsoft\\VisualStudio\\{vsInstanceId}\\ExtensionManager\\EnabledExtensions\";\n    using var key = Registry.CurrentUser.CreateSubKey(keyPath);\n    key?.SetValue(extensionId, 1, RegistryValueKind.DWord);\n}\n```\n\n### Other fix\n\n`SuppressCopilotFreePromoNotification` was called with `devenvPath` but takes no parameters; that call was corrected so the E2E project builds.\n\n### Validation\n\n- **CodeScene** `code_health_review` on `ExperimentalInstanceDeploy.cs`: score **10.0**, no findings.\n- **`make iter`**: build succeeded; the run then failed on the **delta** Code Health step for existing complexity in `TryDismissCopilotPopupUnderMainWindow` in `VisualStudioTestHost.cs`, not for the new registry code.",
